          "body": "God's authorization of Jeremiah is physical before it is verbal. 'The LORD stretched out His hand and touched my mouth' — the same gesture in reverse that the seraph performed for Isaiah with the burning coal (Isaiah 6:6-7). The touch is not metaphorical; it is the visible, bodily sign that the prophet's speech organ has been claimed by YHWH. Then the content is defined: 'Behold, I have put My words in your mouth.' Jeremiah does not compose his messages; he receives them. The implications of this for prophetic authority are enormous — throughout the next forty years, when Jeremiah is accused of lying, treachery, or cowardice, the accusation is ultimately against the God who put those words there. The commission that follows in 1:10 is the most comprehensive in the Hebrew prophets: six verbs covering total authority — four negative (pluck up, break down, destroy, overthrow) and two positive (build and plant). The four-to-two ratio is not accidental; judgment is the dominant note of Jeremiah's ministry, but the minor key of restoration (supremely the new covenant of chapter 31) is never absent."
